#  SaaS Analytics Dashboard

A high-performance, responsive SaaS analytics dashboard built with **React** and **Tailwind CSS**.
This project features centralized state management, real-time data visualization, and a sleek modern UI with full dark mode support.

---

##  Features

### 🔹 Single Source of Truth

Managed via **React Context API** to ensure seamless data synchronization across the entire application.

### 🔹 Role-Based Access Control

Toggle between **Admin** and **Viewer** modes to simulate real-world permission logic.

### 🔹 Dynamic Data Visualization

* Custom **SVG-based Revenue Trend** line graphs
* Interactive **Category Distribution** pie charts

### 🔹 Full CRUD Functionality

* Add, edit, search, and delete orders
* Instant UI updates

### 🔹 Theming

* Persistent **Dark & Light mode**
* Powered by Tailwind CSS + localStorage

### 🔹 Fully Responsive

* Mobile-first design
* Works across all screen sizes

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* **Frontend:** React.js (Hooks, Context API, useMemo)
* **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (Utility-first)
* **Icons:** Lucide-React
* **Build Tool:** Vite

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
src/
├── components/        # Reusable UI components (StatCard, TransactionForm)
├── context/           # Global state management (DashboardContext)
├── pages/             # Main view components (Dashboard)
├── routes/            # Application routing logic
├── assets/            # Static images and styles
└── main.jsx           # Entry point
```

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites

* Node.js (v16 or higher recommended)
* npm or yarn

### Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/nayan-dashboard.git
```

Navigate to the project directory:

```bash
cd nayan-dashboard
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Start the development server:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Open your browser:

```
http://localhost:5173
```

